Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
Plaza Palmera is located in San Diego, California, directly across from the world’s largest land border crossing. Approximately 100,615 people per day (2019) travel northbound through this robust port of entry between the United States and Tijuana, Mexico. 

Plaza Palmera is positioned with incredible visibility and access for the 30,000 people coming through the new pedestrian border crossing and the adjacent transit hub. With its main entrance directly across from PedWest, Plaza Palmera serves as the gateway into San Diego’s largest value shopping district.

For many visitors crossing the border, Plaza Palmera isn’t just their first stop, but it’s also their last shopping and dining destination before returning home.

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: Busiest Land Border Crossing in the US!
